[thinking] **Evaluating test class rules**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm contemplating the rules regarding the one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files. It seems there might be a placeholder class that wasn’t generated, leading to the possibility of having two test files. I realize that the existing JdomTest doesn't map correctly and that JAXP tests shouldn't go there. Also, since all top-level test classes need to be public and there's a violation of this rule, maybe I should adjust that.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Evaluating test class adjustments**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering whether to change the placeholder to a public empty class, especially since there are no JUnit tests. Removing JdomTest might simplify things by reducing unrelated placeholders. But I wonder if there should at least be one test. If we decide to delete it, does that affect our broader testing? 
[thinking] 
[thinking] The final requirement for top-level test classes to be public could mean some might fail after the change. I think editing JdomTest to public could be the less invasive option.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Preparing to add license**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I need to add a license to the project, so I'll use the write tool for that. But wait, before I do that, I should inspect the git status. It’s important to check what changes are currently in the repository to avoid any conflicts or surprises. I want to make sure everything is in the right place before proceeding with adding the license. Let’s get started on this the right way!
[thinking] 
